{
  "name": "RPlog_Man-to-Man",
  "title": "Man to Man",
  "summary": "In the cleared common area of Talon Karrde's base on Myrkr, the jealous mechanic Orson Tighe seeks out the Selas warrior Simon Sezirok, intending to confront him over his growing closeness to Jessalyn Valios. Instead of a quarrel, Simon disarms the tension by offering to show Orson his staff, carved with a rose symbolizing his Force-vision of being bound to Jessalyn, and patiently guides Orson through proper combat form. Orson lets his resentment go, accepting the role of supportive friend, just as Jessalyn herself emerges and joins them, sensing the potential for conflict. Talk turns to their next move, with Simon proposing they split off from Karrde to harry the Empire like wolves, a useful distraction while Karrde hunts the Death Star for the New Republic. When Karrde's associate Drew arrives, the group debates the wisdom of operating in isolation, ultimately leaning toward Simon's plan, and Jessalyn asks Orson to serve as their pilot for whatever comes next.",
